sentences: Grace Burrows was born in Leicester, the daughter of Dr. Benjamin Harper Burrows (1864–1915) who served as organist for a number of churches in the Leicester area.
She was also the sister of composer Benjamin Burrows (1891–1966).
She was appointed as a Lecturer in Music at the University College, Leicester, in 1924.
In 1922 she served as the founding leader of the Leicester Symphony Orchestra, and in 1934 she also conducted the British Women’s Symphony Orchestra.
